content.text:
Let me analyze the structure and help you build it using the blocks from the dictionary.

Target Structure Analysis:
- 3 colors of blocks used: Red, Yellow, Orange
- 2 layers in the structure
- Contains arched/curved red blocks, rectangular yellow blocks, and cylindrical/triangular orange blocks
- Complex arrangement with interlocking blocks

Block Selection from Dictionary:
- Red blocks (Index 1, 2, 3): Arched/curved blocks
- Yellow blocks (Index 4, 5, 6, 7): Rectangular blocks
- Orange blocks (Index 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16): Cylindrical and triangular blocks

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 9 (orange cylinder)
    Step2: Move block with index 9 (second orange cylinder)
    Step3: Move block with index 4 (yellow rectangular block) across the orange cylinders
    Step4: Move block with index 1 (red arched block) next to the yellow block
    Step5: Move block with index 3 (red curved block) adjacent to the first red block
    Step6: Move block with index 5 (yellow rectangular block) to connect the red blocks
    Step7: Move block with index 16 (orange triangular block) on top of the orange cylinders
}
